        <div class="category">
            <div class="category-title">üîç 1. INFORMATION GATHERING (Raccolta Informazioni)</div>
            
            <!-- NMAP -->
            <div class="tool">
                <div class="tool-name">NMAP - Network Mapper</div>
                
                <div class="tool-description">
                    Il tool di network scanning pi√π famoso e potente al mondo, creato da Gordon Lyon (Fyodor). √à lo standard de facto per la scoperta di host, porte, servizi e vulnerabilit√†. Supporta oltre 600 script NSE (Nmap Scripting Engine) per task avanzati come vulnerability detection, exploitation e backdoor discovery.
                </div>
                
                <div class="tool-uses">
                    <strong>üìå Usi Principali:</strong> Port scanning, service/version detection, OS fingerprinting, vulnerability scanning, network mapping, firewall evasion testing, network inventory
                </div>
                
                <div class="section-title">üîß Funzionalit√† Chiave</div>
                <ul class="feature-list">
                    <li><strong>Port Scanning:</strong> TCP/UDP/SCTP con tecniche stealth (SYN, FIN, NULL, Xmas, Idle scan)</li>
                    <li><strong>Service Detection (-sV):</strong> Identifica versioni esatte dei servizi in ascolto</li>
                    <li><strong>OS Detection (-O):</strong> Fingerprinting avanzato del sistema operativo</li>
                    <li><strong>NSE Scripts:</strong> Oltre 600 script per vulnerability detection, brute force, discovery</li>
                    <li><strong>Timing Templates:</strong> Da T0 (paranoid) a T5 (insane) per controllo velocit√†</li>
                    <li><strong>Output Formats:</strong> Normal, XML, grepable, script kiddie</li>
                    <li><strong>Firewall Evasion:</strong> Fragmentazione, decoys, source port manipulation</li>
                </ul>
                
                <div class="section-title">üíª Esempi Pratici</div>
                
                <div class="example-title">üéØ Esempio 1: Scan Base con Service Detection</div>
                <div class="command-block"><span class="comment"># Scan standard con rilevamento versioni servizi</span>
<span class="command">nmap -sV 192.168.1.100</span>

<span class="comment"># Output esempio:</span>
<span class="output">PORT     STATE SERVICE    VERSION
22/tcp   open  ssh        OpenSSH 8.2p1 Ubuntu
80/tcp   open  http       Apache httpd 2.4.41
3306/tcp open  mysql      MySQL 5.7.33</span></div>

                <div class="example-title">üéØ Esempio 2: Scan Completo Aggressivo</div>
                <div class="command-block"><span class="comment"># -A: Abilita OS detection, version detection, script scanning e traceroute</span>
<span class="command">nmap -A -T4 192.168.1.100</span>

<span class="comment"># T4: Timing template "aggressive" per scan veloce</span>
<span class="comment"># Include: -O (OS detection), -sV (version), -sC (default scripts), --traceroute</span></div>

                <div class="example-title">üéØ Esempio 3: Scan Tutte le Porte</div>
                <div class="command-block"><span class="comment"># Scan completo di tutte le 65535 porte TCP</span>
<span class="command">nmap -p- 192.168.1.100</span>

<span class="comment"># Con service detection e timing veloce</span>
<span class="command">nmap -p- -sV -T4 192.168.1.100</span>

<span class="comment"># Solo top 1000 porte (default)</span>
<span class="command">nmap 192.168.1.100</span></div>

                <div class="example-title">üéØ Esempio 4: Stealth SYN Scan</div>
                <div class="command-block"><span class="comment"># SYN scan (half-open): pi√π stealth, richiede privilegi root</span>
<span class="command">sudo nmap -sS 192.168.1.100</span>

<span class="comment"># Non completa il TCP handshake, meno rilevabile dai log</span>
<span class="comment"># Pi√π veloce del connect() scan normale</span></div>

                <div class="example-title">üéØ Esempio 5: Scan Vulnerabilit√† con NSE</div>
                <div class="command-block"><span class="comment"># Esegue tutti gli script di categoria "vuln"</span>
<span class="command">nmap --script vuln 192.168.1.100</span>

<span class="comment"># Script specifici per vulnerabilit√† comuni</span>
<span class="command">nmap --script http-vuln-* 192.168.1.100</span>

<span class="comment"># SQL injection detection</span>
<span class="command">nmap --script http-sql-injection 192.168.1.100</span>

<span class="comment"># EternalBlue (MS17-010) check</span>
<span class="command">nmap --script smb-vuln-ms17-010 192.168.1.100</span></div>

                <div class="example-title">üéØ Esempio 6: Scan Intera Subnet</div>
                <div class="command-block"><span class="comment"># Scan subnet /24 (254 host)</span>
<span class="command">nmap -sV -T4 192.168.1.0/24</span>

<span class="comment"># Solo discovery host vivi (no port scan)</span>
<span class="command">nmap -sn 192.168.1.0/24</span>

<span class="comment"># Output su file XML per parsing</span>
<span class="command">nmap -sV 192.168.1.0/24 -oX scan_results.xml</span></div>

                <div class="example-title">üéØ Esempio 7: OS Detection</div>
                <div class="command-block"><span class="comment"># Rileva sistema operativo</span>
<span class="command">sudo nmap -O 192.168.1.100</span>

<span class="comment"># Con aggressive detection</span>
<span class="command">sudo nmap -O --osscan-guess 192.168.1.100</span>

<span class="output"># Output esempio:
Running: Linux 4.X|5.X
OS CPE: cpe:/o:linux:linux_kernel:4 cpe:/o:linux:linux_kernel:5
OS details: Linux 4.15 - 5.6</span></div>

                <div class="example-title">üéØ Esempio 8: UDP Scan (Lento ma Importante)</div>
                <div class="command-block"><span class="comment"># UDP scan top 1000 porte (MOLTO lento)</span>
<span class="command">sudo nmap -sU 192.168.1.100</span>

<span class="comment"># UDP scan porte specifiche comuni</span>
<span class="command">sudo nmap -sU -p 53,67,68,161,162,500 192.168.1.100</span>

<span class="comment"># Combinato TCP + UDP scan</span>
<span class="command">sudo nmap -sS -sU -p T:80,443,U:53,161 192.168.1.100</span></div>

                <div class="example-title">üéØ Esempio 9: Firewall Evasion</div>
                <div class="command-block"><span class="comment"># Fragmentazione pacchetti per evitare firewall</span>
<span class="command">nmap -f 192.168.1.100</span>

<span class="comment"># Decoy scan: nasconde IP reale tra IP fake</span>
<span class="command">nmap -D RND:10 192.168.1.100</span>
<span class="comment"># Genera 10 IP random come decoy</span>

<span class="comment"># Source port manipulation</span>
<span class="command">nmap --source-port 53 192.168.1.100</span>
<span class="comment"># Usa porta sorgente 53 (DNS) spesso permessa da firewall</span></div>

                <div class="example-title">üéØ Esempio 10: Script NSE Specifici</div>
                <div class="command-block"><span class="comment"># HTTP enumeration completo</span>
<span class="command">nmap --script http-enum,http-headers,http-methods 192.168.1.100</span>

<span class="comment"># SMB enumeration</span>
<span class="command">nmap --script smb-enum-shares,smb-enum-users 192.168.1.100</span>

<span class="comment"># Brute force SSH</span>
<span class="command">nmap --script ssh-brute --script-args userdb=users.txt,passdb=pass.txt 192.168.1.100</span>

<span class="comment"># Heartbleed vulnerability check</span>
<span class="command">nmap --script ssl-heartbleed 192.168.1.100</span></div>
            </div>

            <!-- WIRESHARK -->
            <div class="tool">
                <div class="tool-name">Wireshark</div>
                
                <div class="tool-description">
                    L'analizzatore di protocollo di rete pi√π popolare e potente al mondo. Cattura traffico live da interfacce di rete e permette deep packet inspection con dissector per oltre 2000 protocolli. Interfaccia grafica intuitiva con filtri display e capture estremamente potenti. Essenziale per network troubleshooting, analisi malware, forensics e security assessment.
                </div>
                
                <div class="tool-uses">
                    <strong>üìå Usi Principali:</strong> Network troubleshooting, protocol analysis, forensics di rete, malware analysis, debugging applicazioni, security auditing, packet inspection dettagliato
                </div>
                
                <div class="section-title">üîß Funzionalit√† Chiave</div>
                <ul class="feature-list">
                    <li><strong>Live Capture:</strong> Cattura pacchetti in tempo reale da interfacce multiple</li>
                    <li><strong>Deep Inspection:</strong> Analisi dettagliata di 2000+ protocolli di rete</li>
                    <li><strong>Display Filters:</strong> Filtri potentissimi per isolare traffico specifico</li>
                    <li><strong>Follow Streams:</strong> Ricostruzione completa di sessioni TCP/UDP/HTTP/TLS</li>
                    <li><strong>Export Objects:</strong> Estrazione file, immagini, documenti dal traffico HTTP</li>
                    <li><strong>Statistics:</strong> Grafici e statistiche dettagliate del traffico</li>
                    <li><strong>Colorization:</strong> Colorazione pacchetti per identificazione rapida</li>
                    <li><strong>PCAP Analysis:</strong> Analisi offline di file PCAP salvati</li>
                </ul>
                
                <div class="section-title">üíª Esempi Pratici</div>
                
                <div class="example-title">üéØ Esempio 1: Avvio e Cattura Base</div>
                <div class="command-block"><span class="comment"># Avvio Wireshark GUI</span>
<span class="command">wireshark</span>

<span class="comment"># Cattura su interfaccia specifica</span>
<span class="command">wireshark -i eth0</span>

<span class="comment"># Avvio con file PCAP esistente</span>
<span class="command">wireshark capture.pcap</span>

<span class="comment"># Lista interfacce disponibili</span>
<span class="command">wireshark -D</span></div>

                <div class="example-title">üéØ Esempio 2: Filtri Display Essenziali</div>
                <div class="command-block"><span class="comment"># ===== FILTRI PROTOCOLLO =====</span>

<span class="comment"># Solo traffico HTTP</span>
http

<span class="comment"># Solo traffico HTTPS/TLS</span>
tls

<span class="comment"># Solo DNS queries/responses</span>
dns

<span class="comment"># Solo FTP</span>
ftp

<span class="comment"># Solo SSH</span>
ssh

<span class="comment"># ===== FILTRI IP =====</span>

<span class="comment"># Traffico da/verso IP specifico</span>
ip.addr == 192.168.1.100

<span class="comment"># Solo traffico da IP sorgente</span>
ip.src == 192.168.1.100

<span class="comment"># Solo traffico verso IP destinazione</span>
ip.dst == 192.168.1.100

<span class="comment"># Range di IP</span>
ip.addr >= 192.168.1.0 and ip.addr <= 192.168.1.255

<span class="comment"># ===== FILTRI PORTE =====</span>

<span class="comment"># Traffico su porta 80 (HTTP)</span>
tcp.port == 80

<span class="comment"># Porte multiple</span>
tcp.port == 80 || tcp.port == 443 || tcp.port == 8080

<span class="comment"># Porta sorgente specifica</span>
tcp.srcport == 12345

<span class="comment"># Porta destinazione</span>
tcp.dstport == 443</div>

                <div class="example-title">üéØ Esempio 3: Filtri TCP Avanzati</div>
                <div class="command-block"><span class="comment"># Pacchetti con flag SYN (inizio connessione)</span>
tcp.flags.syn == 1

<span class="comment"># Solo SYN senza ACK (nuove connessioni)</span>
tcp.flags.syn == 1 and tcp.flags.ack == 0

<span class="comment"># Pacchetti RST (connessione rifiutata/resettata)</span>
tcp.flags.reset == 1

<span class="comment"># TCP retransmissions (problemi di rete)</span>
tcp.analysis.retransmission

<span class="comment"># Pacchetti duplicati</span>
tcp.analysis.duplicate_ack</div>

                <div class="example-title">üéØ Esempio 4: Cattura Credenziali in Chiaro</div>
                <div class="command-block"><span class="comment"># HTTP Basic Authentication (username:password in chiaro!)</span>
http.authbasic

<span class="comment"># FTP LOGIN credentials</span>
ftp.request.command == "USER" || ftp.request.command == "PASS"

<span class="comment"># Ricerca parola "password" nei pacchetti</span>
frame contains "password"

<span class="comment"># Ricerca "login" case-insensitive</span>
frame matches "(?i)login"

<span class="comment"># POST requests (spesso contengono form data)</span>
http.request.method == "POST"</div>

                <div class="example-title">üéØ Esempio 5: Analisi HTTP</div>
                <div class="command-block"><span class="comment"># Tutte le richieste HTTP GET</span>
http.request.method == "GET"

<span class="comment"># Richieste POST con form data</span>
http.request.method == "POST"

<span class="comment"># Errori HTTP (4xx e 5xx)</span>
http.response.code >= 400

<span class="comment"># Solo HTTP 200 OK</span>
http.response.code == 200

<span class="comment"># Richieste a dominio specifico</span>
http.host == "example.com"

<span class="comment"># Cookie nel traffico HTTP</span>
http.cookie

<span class="comment"># User-Agent specifico</span>
http.user_agent contains "Mozilla"</div>

                <div class="example-title">üéØ Esempio 6: Follow TCP Stream</div>
                <div class="command-block"><span class="comment"># WORKFLOW per vedere conversazione completa:</span>

1. Trova pacchetto interessante (es. HTTP request)
2. Click destro -> Follow -> TCP Stream
3. Visualizza intera conversazione client-server
4. Utile per vedere:
   - Contenuto completo richieste/risposte HTTP
   - Sessioni FTP con comandi e file
   - Dati trasferiti in chiaro

<span class="comment"># Shortcut: Ctrl+Alt+Shift+T su pacchetto selezionato</span></div>

                <div class="example-title">üéØ Esempio 7: Export HTTP Objects</div>
                <div class="command-block"><span class="comment"># Estrai file scaricati via HTTP</span>

1. File -> Export Objects -> HTTP
2. Visualizza lista tutti gli oggetti HTTP catturati
3. Salva singoli file o tutti
4. Utile per:
   - Estrarre file scaricati
   - Salvare immagini visualizzate
   - Recuperare documenti trasferiti

<span class="comment"># Supporta anche: IMF (email), SMB, DICOM</span></div>

                <div class="example-title">üéØ Esempio 8: Filtri DNS</div>
                <div class="command-block"><span class="comment"># Tutte le query DNS</span>
dns.flags.response == 0

<span class="comment"># Solo risposte DNS</span>
dns.flags.response == 1

<span class="comment"># Query per dominio specifico</span>
dns.qry.name == "example.com"

<span class="comment"># Query DNS type A (IPv4)</span>
dns.qry.type == 1

<span class="comment"># Query DNS type AAAA (IPv6)</span>
dns.qry.type == 28

<span class="comment"># DNS query che contiene stringa</span>
dns.qry.name contains "malware"</div>

                <div class="example-title">üéØ Esempio 9: Statistiche Utili</div>
                <div class="command-block"><span class="comment"># Statistics menu offre analisi potenti:</span>

<span class="comment"># Protocol Hierarchy</span>
Statistics -> Protocol Hierarchy
<span class="comment"># Mostra % di ogni protocollo nel traffico catturato</span>

<span class="comment"># Conversations</span>
Statistics -> Conversations
<span class="comment"># Lista tutte le conversazioni tra IP</span>

<span class="comment"># Endpoints</span>
Statistics -> Endpoints
<span class="comment"># Lista tutti gli host comunicanti</span>

<span class="comment"># HTTP Statistics</span>
Statistics -> HTTP -> Requests
<span class="comment"># Statistiche dettagliate richieste HTTP</span>

<span class="comment"># I/O Graph</span>
Statistics -> I/O Graph
<span class="comment"># Grafico traffico nel tempo</span></div>

                <div class="example-title">üéØ Esempio 10: Capture Filters (BPF Syntax)</div>
                <div class="command-block"><span class="comment"># Capture filters si applicano DURANTE la cattura</span>
<span class="comment"># Sintassi Berkeley Packet Filter (BPF)</span>

<span class="comment"># Cattura solo HTTP</span>
port 80

<span class="comment"># Cattura HTTP e HTTPS</span>
port 80 or port 443

<span class="comment"># Cattura traffico da/verso host</span>
host 192.168.1.100

<span class="comment"># Cattura solo traffico da host</span>
src host 192.168.1.100

<span class="comment"># Cattura subnet</span>
net 192.168.1.0/24

<span class="comment"># Esclude traffico SSH (per ridurre rumore)</span>
not port 22

<span class="comment"># Solo TCP traffic</span>
tcp

<span class="comment"># Solo UDP traffic</span>
udp</div>
            </div>

            <!-- BURP SUITE -->
            <div class="tool">
